        <h3 class="mt-h3" data-reveal>
          The Main Thread is just a Looper thread
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-prose" data-reveal>
          There's nothing magic about the UI thread. It was prepared as a Looper
          thread before your app's code ran, and every touch, draw and callback
          is a message on its queue. Which is why this works from anywhere:
        </p>
        <pre class="mt-code" data-reveal><code>{codeMainHandler}</code></pre>

        <h3 class="mt-h3" data-reveal>Synchronising with VSYNC</h3>
        <p class="mt-prose" data-reveal>
          Animations can't just update whenever — they'd tear or waste frames.
          The <code>Choreographer</code> posts frame callbacks aligned to the display's
          <strong>VSYNC</strong> pulse (~16.6ms at 60Hz), and
          <code>ValueAnimator</code> computes its value once per pulse. One heartbeat
          drives every animation in sync:
        </p>
